Add memory control for MergeReader
body:
In this pr, I extract interface MemoryReservationManager. MemoryReservationManager is used to reserve/release memory from LocalExecutionPlanner#freeMemoryForOperators during planning and execution stage. This pr adds memory control logic of PriorityMergeReader.
One FI may have multiple SeriesScanUtils, each FI only has one MemoryReservationManager and the SeriesScanUtils use MemoryReservationManagerWrapper to queue the reserve/release operations.
The most important thing is to make sure reservedBytesIntal of MemoryReservationManager is correctly returned to freeMemoryForOperators.

Pipe: Filter devices by pattern before reading device metadata from TsFile
body:
Currently we read the metadata of **all** devices and measurements when constructing a TsFileInsertionDataContainer. This is both time-consuming and memory-wasting if only **a few** devices match the pattern. This PR filters the devices by pattern before reading the metadata of devices and measurements, saving memory and I/O cost when there are many unmatched devices.

Note: this only works when TsFile metadata are **not** cached (due to high memory usage of TsFile metadata cache), because cached metadata can not be filtered so that pipes with arbitrary patterns can use it.

title: [IOTDB-6339] Optimize the time slice control of SeriesScanOperator and AlignedSeriesScanOperator
body:
Previously, we will scan until we get at least one satisfied row and then we have chance to do time slice control.
However, when we do the predicate push down optimization, we may need much more time to get a satisfied row from tsfile, so we need to change the control processing of SeriesScanOperator and AlignedSeriesScanOperator.

2. we find that when restarting or stopping consensusPipeTask, the connector doesn't release events' reference in transferBuffer, causing WALs being pinned all the time. This pr fixed it.

title: Support active schema query
body:
## Description

This PR has accomplished three things. 

1. I added a device-level interface fetch to IFetchSchema and implemented it. Originally, there were many fields in `SchemaFetchStatement` designed for measurements. Therefore, I renamed it to `SeriesSchemaFetchStatement`, added a new `DeviceSchemaFetchStatement`, and retained the common parts as the abstract class SchemaFetchStatement. 
2. I modified the fetch measurement schema interface in `IFetchSchemaFetcher` to fully retrieve all the original data of the series, such as alias, tags, attributes, etc. This interface is specifically designed for active schema queries. 

  **Note: To implement this interface, some changes were made to the serialization method of the underlying ClusterSchemaTree, which will make the system unable to support rolling upgrades!** 

3. I found and fixed some bugs in the active schema query. And corresponding IT has been added.
    * The `show devices` command could not correctly display the template and TTL. 
    * Permissions were not considered (active schema queries require corresponding `READ_SCHEMA` and `READ_DATA` permissions for the series). 
    * TTL was not properly considered (not fixed in this PR, TODO).
